## Rules & Scoring

• The shortest program (in bytes, in any programming language) that eventually outputs the answer with community approval is the winner.
• If we end up having the same winner multiple times, then the winner will be the product of all winning answers.
• The winner will have a score of 2
• If they changed their answer, for example, to output 0, their score will be 0
